cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with convolutional neural networks and their application in computer vision tasks, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques to optimize network architecture, which falls under cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper proposes a new convolution filter that reduces the number of parameters in the network, which is related to optimization techniques in neural networks and falls under cs.NE. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on various computer vision tasks, including image classification and semantic segmentation, which are subfields of cs.MM.
